strings: <se_low>Yangus: It's funny 'ow the Godbird's nest is 'ere in this world, even though she ain't 'ere 'erself.
<se_low>Yangus: It ain't funny 'ow knackerin' it is to climb up 'ere, though.
<se_high>Jessica: Now that we're able to fly freely, we can go anywhere. Even places like this that we couldn't reach before.
<se_high>Jessica: I wonder if there are other remote and inaccessible places out there? We should try to find them! We might discover something new!
<se_def>Angelo: The Godbird's soulstone must be a dream come true for a detour-lover like you, <hero>! But this is going a bit far even for you!
<se_def>Angelo: Not all of us are born wanderers, you know! Spare a thought for us folk who aren't quite as partial to scaling great heights as you are!
<se_def>Angelo: If we're allowing ourselves to be sidetracked, how about sidetracking in the direction of a casino? I mean, how's a man supposed to resist those bingo healslimes?
<se_low>Yangus: This mountain's pretty tall, eh? Maybe Rhapthorne's floatin' castle'll bump into it!?

<se_low>Yangus: That'd bring 'im crashin' down to earth!
An' it'd save us a bit o' trouble wiv all that flyin' malarkey, an' all!
<se_high>Jessica: Why did we use a precious gift like the Godbird's soulstone to come to a place like this!?

<se_high>Jessica: Don't we have more important work to do?
You know, like getting to the floating castle and defeating Rhapthorne?
<se_def>Angelo: The climb up to the nest is hardly what you'd call a gentle stroll.
<se_def>Angelo: Why have you dragged us all the way up here, anyway!? We're not mountaineers, you know!
<se_low>Yangus: This mountain's pretty tall, eh? Maybe Rhapthorne'll bump into it one day when 'e's floatin' past!?
<se_high>Jessica: Why did we use a precious gift like the Godbird's soulstone to come to a place like this!?

<se_high>Jessica: Listen. We've got more important things to do.
We need to use Empyrea's power to defeat Rhapthorne in his new form! Remember?
<se_def>Angelo: The climb up to the nest is hardly what you'd call a gentle stroll.
<se_def>Angelo: Why have you dragged us all the way up here, anyway!? We're not mountaineers, you know!

<se_high>Red: So wot's really the diff'rence between the two
worlds then, eh? Just the colours? Or lack of,
I should say.

<se_high>Red: Not that I'm really bothered, mind.
Just tryin' to make conversation.
<se_low>Morrie: If we can fly in the sky, the world is in the sweaty palm of my hands! Think of the new monsters we can meet and invite to my monstrous pit!
<se_high>Red: All right, wot is it, then? Wot ya got up yer sleeve? There's gotta be some reason you've brought us all 'ere, right?
<se_high>Red: Or are you some kinda weirdo wot likes climbin' mountains wiv no flamin' treasure up 'em!?
<se_low>Morrie: Si, a FANTASTICO plan! Before the final slowdown of the Rhapthorne, we build up our muscoli with a walk up the mountain!

<se_low>Morrie: Allora! We make it a race, ay?
Last one to the top is a pamby-namby!
